children.subject: Do you think that you will be prepared for recruiting with just CS 61A and 70 without having taken CS 61B?

history.content: Hi! I am thinking about which of these two courses to take along with 61B + 170 next fall, plus recruiting. I'll most probably take Data 100 on later semesters, so I think I won't lose the chance to study the materials for data 8. So, I just want to have an idea about which of the two courses is more easy to get a A lol. I expect that data 8 is easy after taking 61A and 70, but the berkeleytime shows that astron C10 actually has a higher A rate (41% vs 32%). Does Astron C10 requires lots of memorizing, like some humanities courses, or is it more like a physics course? Thanks!
history.subject: Data 8 vs Astron C10 difficulty comparison?
